LDTEXT:
Onsite to return station back to normal operation:

@16:40- notified by CPD (Rafi) and Consultant (Jake GEI) that the work has been completed- will begin reverting station back to normal operation

@17:00- discharge isolation valve in driveway reopened 

@17:10- returned all station pumps and FCV back into auto- informed ROC 

Station back to normal operation- informed oncall operator (Jason Garnett) 

Station/equipment- Ok

@17:41 - ROC called for CO2 adjusted PH Lolo alarm, interlocking the low lift pumps.  
Reviewed SCADA trends, analyzer experienced a sudden drop from 7.1 to 6.2.  There is also filter #2 currently in backwash.  
@17:55 - placed high lift pumps to manual off, and closed the effluent valve on filter #1, as there is no flow going to the pre treatment as low lifts are interlocked.  
@17:55 - settled water conduit low alarm also came in.
Will monitor CO2 adjusted pH for now, and see if it recovers.  Plant is in manual off.
@18:11 - CO2 adjusted PH is 6.7.  Cleared alarm, and low lift pumps restarted.  Monitoring plant while the pretreatment is filling again and the backwash finished.  
Placed filter #1 effluent valve back to auto @18:34.  Filter back to production.
Duty is almost to stop setpoint, will leave the plant off for the night so central team can investigate tomorrow on site if there are further issues. 
Informed ROC, alarms cleared, plant in manual off for the night

On site for station check, lab analysis and weekly micro sampling (W11483538)
Reviewed MIT and daily filter performance on all membrane trains - all passed and within range - recorded readings in PWQ sheets 

Attempted to exercise backpulse tank #1 fill valve @10:39 - it failed to open.  On call Op had experienced issues with it over the holiday break.  

Duty rotated clearwell chlorinators @11:30, placed chlorinator #5 to D1.  Switched clearwell solenoid valve from #2 to #1
Duty rotated raw water sampling pumps - placed P3 to D1

Completed washwater and water to lake analyzer maintenance - cleaned cl2 analyzers and TSS probe - no issues 
Verified analyzers in basement: Contact tanks, clearwells, treated, residual management
Grab / Analyzer (Mg/L)
@12:13 CT#1: 2.01 / 1.94
@12:15 CT#2: 2.13 / 2.19
@12:18 CW#1: 1.77 / 1.66 - Adjusted to 1.77 based on grab residuals 
@12:20 CW#2: 1.54 / 1.50 
@12:24 Post CW: 1.85 / 1.63 - Adjusted to 1.85 based on grabs 
@12:33 Keswick Free: 1.81 / 1.86
@12:33 Keswick Total: 2.06 / 2.06 
@12:30 Sutton Free: 1.79 / 1.75 
@12:30 Sutton Total: 2.09 / 2.08

Collected weekly micro samples @12:40 (Raw and Treated)
Completed PWQ sheets, data collection and lab data sheets 

Exercised backpulse tank fill vlave #2 again.  Found that the actuator body itself was moving while the valve was trying to open.  Found that the bolts holding the actuator on the valve were loose.  Tightened bolts, exercised valve locally and on SCADA, opened and closed okay.  Placed vlave back to auto, in duty 2 
Reviewed trends
Equipment OOS: Sludge P3, Bisulfite P2
Station ok

On site for station check, lab analysis and to collect weekly micro samples (W11469988)
Reviewed MIT and daily / monthly filter performance on all membrane trains - all passed and within range - recorded readings into PWQ sheets

Initiated Recovery Clean Hypo on Train #2 @09:00 - it has the highest TMP numbers of all trains, and has had reoccuring TMP alarms recently

- Observed that Keswick head fluoride is reading higher than normal at 0.97 mg/L. Duty was just activated @09:02, plant will start soon.  Placed Fluoride pumps 1/2 to manual off while the plant starts, will place pumps back to auto once fluoride level drops.  Placed fluoride pumps back to auto @09:18. P1 started.
- Completed Low lift station check and mussel plate inspection.  Verified low lift analyzers.  Duty rotated raw water sampling pumps - placed P1 to D1.

@09:45 - Activated Sutton ET duty - tower level is 69%.  Cleared fluoride low alarm

- Duty rotated clearwell chlorinators @10:12 - Placed Chlorinator #6 in D1.  Also rotated Clearwell Solenoid valve from #1 to #2.  Inspected Rotameter / Ejector performance.  No issues observed
- Duty rotated air compressors - placed BOGE compressor in lead duty
- Collected first grab sample from train #2 recovery clean @10:40: Cl2 = 440 mg/L, pH = 9.98

Verifications of basement chlorine analyzers: (Grab / Analyzer reading)
@11:42 Contact #1: 2.09 mg/L / 2.01 mg/L
@11:45 Contact #2: 2.04 mg/L / 1.96 mg/L 
@11:47 Clearwell #1: 1.83 mg/L / 1.71 mg/L - Adjusted based on grab residual
@11:52 Clearwell #2: 2.52 mg/L / 2.44 mg/L
Post Clearwell: 2.00 mg/L / 1.52 mg/L - Adjusted based on grab residual
@12:12 Keswick Free: 1.97 mg/L / 2.01 mg/L 
@12:12 Keswick Total: 2.20 mg/L / 2.25 mg/L
@12:18 Sutton Free: 2.01 mg/L / 1.94 mg/L 
@12:18 Sutton Total: 2.34 mg/L / 2.29 mg/L
Collected Raw and Treated micro samples @12:26 (YD #W11469988)

- Collected second grab sample from train #2 recovery clean @12:30: Cl2 = 450 mg/L, pH = 9.70
- @12:40: Adjusted Keswick Header fluoride from 0.77 mg/L to 0.63 mg/L 

- Completed Plant PWQ sheets and data collected, chemical dosages all okay
- Completed Lab data sheets for Raw and Treated headers
- Cleaned citric acid tank and containment area to prepare for citric acid recovery cleans.  Prepared citric acid solution for R-clean tomorrow 

Reviewed trends, no abnormalities observed 
Equipment OOS: Bisulfite P2, Sludge P3
Station ok
